{"type":"text","timestamp":1773433463159,"sessionID":"ses_31723c3edffeZ3kLyww6Ny5sNi","part":{"id":"prt_ce8deff1f001X99MziDX0o40xe","sessionID":"ses_31723c3edffeZ3kLyww6Ny5sNi","messageID":"msg_ce8def457001k6vs56doU4At9x","type":"text","text":"All tasks are complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### `src/config.ts`\n- Added `cacheTTL: number` field to `AgentRegistryConfig` interface with JSDoc explaining it's in milliseconds\n- Added default value `24 * 60 * 60 * 1000` (24 hours) to `DEFAULT_CONFIG.agentRegistry.cacheTTL`\n\n### `src/lib/agent-registry.ts`\nNew exports:\n1. **`RegistryAgentInfo`** — Interface for agent listing results with `agentType`, `name`, `category`, and `description` fields\n2. **`listRegistryAgents(source)`** — Fetches the repo structure via GitHub Contents API, walks category directories in parallel, downloads each `.md` file to extract the description from YAML frontmatter. Excludes non-agent directories (`.github`, `scripts`, `examples`)\n3. **`getCachedAgents(projectRoot, config)`** — Recursively scans `.wombo-combo/agents-cache/` for `.md` files, extracts metadata from frontmatter, returns `RegistryAgentInfo[]`\n\nEnhanced existing functions:\n4. **TTL-based cache validation** — Added `isCacheValid()` helper that checks file mtime against `config.agentRegistry.cacheTTL`. `resolveAgentForTask()` now only uses cache when within TTL\n5. **Offline fallback** — `resolveAgentForTask()` now wraps the fetch in try/catch. On failure, it checks for stale cache (ignoring TTL) and uses it with a warning. Only re-throws if no cache exists at all\n\nInternal helpers:\n- `extractDescription()` — Parses YAML frontmatter to extract the `description` field without requiring the `yaml` package\n- `cacheDir()` — Resolves the cache root directory path\n- `isCacheValid()` — TTL-based cache freshness check using `statSync().mtimeMs`","time":{"start":1773433463157,"end":1773433463157}}}
